edu.uidaho.junicon.interpreter.interpreter

Interface IInterpreterSetters

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IInterpreter
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractShell, CommandShell, JuniconInterpreter, TransformInterpreter

    public interface IInterpreterSetters
    Setters for dependency injection of properties into a transformational interpreter.

      • setIsInteractive

        void setIsInteractive(boolean on)
        Sets if is in interactive mode. This attribute is inherited into delegated sub-interpreters.

      • getIsInteractive

        boolean getIsInteractive()
        Gets if is in interactive mode. Interactive mode means line-by-line user input with a prompt and the capability to erase lines, while the term interpretive means whether to interpret instead of translate or compile.

      • setIsInterpretive

        void setIsInterpretive(boolean on)
        Sets if is in interpretive mode. This attribute is inherited into delegated sub-interpreters.

      • getIsInterpretive

        boolean getIsInterpretive()
        Gets if is in interpretive mode. The term interpretive means whether to interpret instead of translate or compile. Interpretation need not be interactive, for example for aggregate script files.

      • setPrompt

        void setPrompt(String prompt)
        Set prompt.

        boolean getShowRawSubstrateErrors()
        Get if should output raw substrate error messages.

      • setDoNotPreprocess

        void setDoNotPreprocess(boolean on)
        Sets if should not preprocess statements. Will still detect complete statements and parse unless overridden. Will still handle directives. This attribute is inherited into delegated sub-interpreters.

      • getDoNotPreprocess

        boolean getDoNotPreprocess()
        Gets if should not preprocess statements. Will still detect complete statements and parse unless overridden. Will still handle directives.

      • setDoNotDetect

        void setDoNotDetect(boolean on)
        Sets if should not detect complete statements (getParseUnit). Implies do not preprocess. This attribute is inherited into delegated sub-interpreters.

      • getDoNotDetect

        boolean getDoNotDetect()
        Gets if should not detect complete statements (getParseUnit). Implies do not preprocess.

      • setDoNotTransform

        void setDoNotTransform(boolean on)
        Sets if should not transform or parse statements. Can still detect complete statements. This attribute is inherited into delegated sub-interpreters.

      • getDoNotTransform

        boolean getDoNotTransform()
        Gets if should not transform or parse statements. Can still detect complete statements. Will still delegate to subinterpreter if needed.

      • setJustNormalize

        void setJustNormalize(boolean on)
        Sets if should normalize but not further transform statements. Thus only performs a subset of transformations.

      • getJustNormalize

        boolean getJustNormalize()
        Gets if should normalize but not further transform statements. Thus only performs a subset of transformations.

      • setDoNotExecute

        void setDoNotExecute(boolean on)
        Sets if should not execute statements on the scripting substrate. Will still delegate to subinterpreter if needed. This attribute is inherited into delegated sub-interpreters.

      • getDoNotExecute

        boolean getDoNotExecute()
        Gets if should not execute statements on the scripting substrate. Will still delegate to subinterpreter if needed.

      • setIsVerbose

        void setIsVerbose(EnumSet<ILogger.Trace> isVerbose)
        Sets if verbose, i.e., print commands after transform.

      • getIsVerbose

        EnumSet<ILogger.Trace> getIsVerbose()
        Gets if verbose, i.e., print commands after transform. If verbose is detail, prints commands after normalization, and after transform. If preprocessor, print commands after preprocessing.

      • setInheritVerbose

        void setInheritVerbose(EnumSet<ILogger.Trace> isVerbose)
        If true, turns on verbose in sub-interpreters. If on, this attribute is inherited into delegated sub-interpreters.

      • getInheritVerbose

        EnumSet<ILogger.Trace> getInheritVerbose()
        Gets if verbose is turned on and inherited in sub-interpreters.

      • setTransformSupport

        void setTransformSupport(IThreadResource support)
        Set cut-through holding methods used by XSLT transforms. Static methods in the cut-through, used by XSLT, delegate to this current thread's instance. Delegating uses an inheritable thread local, or a resolver if non-null.

        Get cut-through holding methods used by XSLT transforms.
